{"id":"1050","label":"hoverResult","result":{"contents":[{"language":"dart","value":"dart:convert"},{"language":"dart","value":"JsonEncoder JsonEncoder.withIndent(String indent, [Object Function(dynamic) toEncodable])"},{"language":"dart","value":"/// Creates a JSON encoder that creates multi-line JSON.\n///\n/// The encoding of elements of lists and maps are indented and put on separate\n/// lines. The [indent] string is prepended to these elements, once for each\n/// level of indentation.\n///\n/// If [indent] is `null`, the output is encoded as a single line.\n///\n/// The JSON encoder handles numbers, strings, booleans, null, lists and\n/// maps with string keys directly.\n///\n/// Any other object is attempted converted by [toEncodable] to an\n/// object that is of one of the convertible types.\n///\n/// If [toEncodable] is omitted, it defaults to calling `.toJson()` on\n/// the object."}]},"type":"vertex"}
{"-----Comment":"Done emitting imported declaration","id":"1051","label":"","type":"vertex"}
{"-----Comment":"Emitting imported reference to [withIndent]","id":"1052","label":"","type":"vertex"}
{"_debugContainingFile":"package:server/server.dart","_debugName":"withIndent","end":{"line":52,"character":32},"id":"1053","label":"range","start":{"line":52,"character":22},"type":"vertex"}
